UnicodeStrings.StringIdContent: If inverted, moving the look stick up causes the player to look down.
Select the speed at which you look around. Keep in mind that a higher look speed is not necessarily better.
When enabled, this setting causes your view to automatically recenter as you move forward. This is a great setting for newer players not used to manually controlling their view.
Default. This is the default stick configuration recommended by Bungie.
Southpaw. This setting is similar to the default, but the functions of the left and right sticks have been switched. A special option for lefties.
Legacy. This setting hearkens back to the controls of the console first-person shooters of yesteryear.
Legacy Southpaw. This setting swaps left and right sticks from the Legacy setting. An option for ancient lefties.
Default. This is the default button configuration recommended by Bungie.
Southpaw. This setting is similar to the default except the left and right controls are flipped.
Bumper Jumper.  This setting allows you to melee attack by pressing the right bumper, and to jump by pressing the left bumper.
Boxer. If you're tired of hitting the wrong button in the heat of a melee fight, this setting is for you. Instead, you will pull the left trigger to melee attack.
Green Thumb. This setting allows you to melee attack by pressing the right stick.
Walkie Talkie. This setting puts multiplayer team voice broadcasting on the left bumper.
This setting determines how you stay crouched in the game by pressing the left stick. When set to Toggle, one press will cause your player to stay crouched until you press again.
Customize how you control the flying camera when watching a film in flying camera mode.
